				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think the main problem with 7705 regultaor isn't the load current, but how much they overheight. Without any heat sink, they cannot drive more than one hundred of miliamps without overheating.
<br />The one inside the NES is solidify fixed to the metal shield, who seem to be quite accurate for heat power dissipation.
<br />You said puting a second 7705 in parallel or just putting another power supply in you other post ? One other is parallel should work fine, but it would just share the power dissipation between both chips I think. That'd be pretty innacurate, if you need to do something just make your external power supply.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

